text: Nancy Sandra Sinatra (born June 8, 1940) is an American singer and actress. She was born in Jersey City, New Jersey. She is the elder daughter of Frank Sinatra. She is best known for the song "These Boots Are Made for Walkin'". She had a younger brother, Frank Sinatra, Jr. and has a younger sister, Tina Sinatra. == References == Category:1940 births Category:Living people Category:American movie actors Category:Actors from Jersey City, New Jersey Category:Singers from Jersey City, New Jersey Category:Frank Sinatra
